13/07/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A joint US-Bulgarian infantry military exercise begins Tuesday (13 July) at the Novo Selo polygon near the town of Sliven. Participating in the drill will be 900 US soldiers from the Illinois National Guard and 200 Bulgarian infantry soldiers. The exercise is aimed at improving compatibility among NATO members' troops.
In other news, Finance Minister Milen Velchev and Interior Minister Georgi Petkanov opened the reconstructed Kulata checkpoint at the border with Greece on Monday. Officials expect the checkpoint to handle considerable traffic headed to and from the Athens Olympics next month. (Focus.news - 13/07/04; Darik, Mediapool - 12/07/04)
